## Quick reference

| Obligation | Singapore PDPA | Indonesia UU PDP | Thailand PDPA | Malaysia PDPA |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Conduct assessment | Reasonable + expeditious (≤30d guidance) | Per current regs | Per current regs | "As soon as practicable" — 72h benchmark per JPDP Guideline |
| Notify regulator after assessment concludes notifiable | **3 calendar days** (s26D(1)) | 72 hours from awareness | 72 hours from awareness | **72 hours** from discovery (s12B(1) + JPDP Guideline) |
| Notify affected individuals where significant harm | On or after authority notification | All breaches notify subject (Pasal 46) | Per current regs | **Within 7 days** of Commissioner notification (s12B(2) + JPDP Guideline) |
| Suspend user notification on law-enforcement direction | Yes (s26D(6)) | Per current regs | Per current regs | Per Commissioner direction |
| Vendor-as-intermediary / processor notifies controller | Without undue delay (s26C(3)) | Per current regs | s40 — without delay | Vendor DPA must require ≤24h flow-down so controller hits 72h s12B clock |

Penalty for breach of breach-notification obligations:

- **Singapore PDPA:** up to SGD 1M for orgs ≤ SGD 10M SG turnover; **10% of SG turnover** above (s48J(3))
- **Indonesia UU PDP:** up to 2% of annual revenue
- **Thailand PDPA:** up to THB 5M administrative + criminal penalties for severe violations
- **Malaysia PDPA:** failure to notify Commissioner — **RM 250,000 / 2 years** (s12B(3)). Underlying Security Principle (s9) breach attracts **RM 1M / 3 years** (s5(2) post-A1727); director-deeming liability under s133 applies
